1
00:00:01,368 --> 00:00:04,104
♪

2
00:00:04,204 --> 00:00:06,506
Rue: What if you could
go back to the beginning?

3
00:00:06,606 --> 00:00:07,707
Jules.
(Echoing)

4
00:00:07,807 --> 00:00:13,880
♪

5
00:00:13,980 --> 00:00:14,981
I'm Rue.

6
00:00:15,081 --> 00:00:16,282
I'm Jules.

7
00:00:16,383 --> 00:00:20,053
♪

8
00:00:20,153 --> 00:00:21,955
Rue: I had made a new best
friend for the first time

9
00:00:22,055 --> 00:00:23,923
since getting
out of rehab.

10
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:25,525
I was feeling good
about the world.

11
00:00:25,625 --> 00:00:26,559
Leslie:
Take your time.

12
00:00:26,659 --> 00:00:28,294
You've come
a long way.

13
00:00:28,395 --> 00:00:30,663
♪

14
00:00:30,764 --> 00:00:31,931
Jules:
Oh, my God.
Rue:
What?

15
00:00:32,031 --> 00:00:33,266
That's him.

16
00:00:33,366 --> 00:00:34,501
Rue:
That's Nate's dad.

17
00:00:34,601 --> 00:00:40,340
♪

18
00:00:40,440 --> 00:00:41,808
Tyler?

19
00:00:41,908 --> 00:00:47,647
Nate: Don't try to ruin my life,
and I won't have to ruin yours.

20
00:00:47,747 --> 00:00:50,250
If anyone ever tried
to hurt you, I'd kill them.

21
00:00:50,350 --> 00:00:53,186
Maddy: Nate's just, like,
totally ruined my confidence.

22
00:00:53,286 --> 00:00:56,022
Love is super dark,
and no one talks about it.

23
00:00:56,122 --> 00:00:57,590
Bitch, you're
my soulmate.

24
00:00:57,690 --> 00:00:59,292
Both:
Thank you!

25
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,860
Lexi:
Rue seems really good.

26
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:02,629
It's because of you,
you know?

27
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:05,765
Does the way you feel about her
remind you of anything?

28
00:01:05,865 --> 00:01:08,601
Rue: Every time I feel good,
I think it'll last forever.

29
00:01:08,701 --> 00:01:10,303
But it doesn't.

30
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:11,671
What if we just
fuckin' left?

31
00:01:11,771 --> 00:01:14,474
♪

32
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,475
We're good.

33
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:16,976
Come on.

34
00:01:17,077 --> 00:01:19,579
She left you at
a train station?

35
00:01:19,679 --> 00:01:20,613
Rue:
Yeah.

36
00:01:20,713 --> 00:01:22,282
Faye:
Holy fucking shit.

37
00:01:22,382 --> 00:01:24,250
♪

38
00:01:24,350 --> 00:01:27,487
Rue: However hard
life was, it got harder.

39
00:01:27,587 --> 00:01:29,522
♪

40
00:01:29,622 --> 00:01:31,458
I relapsed.

41
00:01:31,558 --> 00:01:36,362
♪

42
00:01:36,463 --> 00:01:41,401
If I were a genius, I'd figure
out a way to do drugs for free.

43
00:01:41,501 --> 00:01:44,204
Rue, ready to do
some business?

44
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:46,706
♪

45
00:01:46,806 --> 00:01:50,043
For the first time in my life,
I'm doing something for myself.

46
00:01:50,143 --> 00:01:51,845
Fezco: (Over phone)
Of course I'ma be there.

47
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:53,746
I'ma be sittin'
in the front row.

48
00:01:53,847 --> 00:02:00,520
♪

49
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:03,456
Maddy: I'm gonna get
back together with Nate.

50
00:02:03,556 --> 00:02:07,293
Hey, Cass, how long have you
been fucking Nate Jacobs?

51
00:02:07,393 --> 00:02:09,162
Open the door,
Cassie!

52
00:02:11,231 --> 00:02:14,501
The longer you do drugs,
the more you're gonna lose.

53
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,469
Leslie:
Jules told me everything.

54
00:02:16,569 --> 00:02:18,037
Rue:
What did you do with them?

55
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:21,040
Jules:
We flushed 'em down the toilet.

56
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,709
You are fuckin'
dead to me.

57
00:02:22,809 --> 00:02:25,745
♪

58
00:02:25,845 --> 00:02:29,249
This is the part where
the character never recovers.

59
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:32,085
When do you think you're
gonna come up with the cash?

60
00:02:32,185 --> 00:02:33,987
Rue: This is the scene
that scars her forever.

61
00:02:34,087 --> 00:02:35,288
Don't shoot,
don't shoot!

62
00:02:35,388 --> 00:02:37,524
There's a kid in here!

63
00:02:37,624 --> 00:02:38,591
(Gunshot)

64
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:42,328
I got faith in you.

65
00:02:42,428 --> 00:02:44,230
♪

66
00:02:51,704 --> 00:02:53,572
[Rue]
A lot of people ask
what I've been up to

67
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:54,908
since high school.

68
00:02:56,309 --> 00:02:58,978
And honestly,
nothing good.

69
00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:02,982
[people shouting in Spanish]

70
00:03:04,784 --> 00:03:07,486
[shouting in Spanish continues]

71
00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:09,489
[engine revving]

72
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,458
Más fuerte.

73
00:03:13,459 --> 00:03:16,061
[engine revving]

74
00:03:16,062 --> 00:03:18,264
[shouting in Spanish continues]

75
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,868
Gracias, mi amigos!
[laughing]

76
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:25,038
- [engine revving]
- [all cheering]

77
00:03:26,105 --> 00:03:28,607
[♪ "Ride Like the Wind"
by Christopher Cross playing]

78
00:03:28,608 --> 00:03:31,043
- [volume increasing]
- Whoo!

79
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:35,147
♪ It is the night,
my body's weak ♪

80
00:03:35,148 --> 00:03:37,951
♪ I'm on the run,
no time to sleep ♪

81
00:03:38,818 --> 00:03:42,487
- ♪ I've got to ride,
ride like the wind ♪
- [Rue laughing]

82
00:03:42,488 --> 00:03:45,225
[singing along]
♪ To be free again ♪

83
00:03:46,492 --> 00:03:49,828
♪ And I've got such
a long way to go ♪

84
00:03:49,829 --> 00:03:51,463
♪ Such a long way to go ♪

85
00:03:51,464 --> 00:03:54,366
♪ To make it to the border
of Mexico ♪

86
00:03:54,367 --> 00:03:58,103
♪ So I'll ride like the wind ♪

87
00:03:58,104 --> 00:03:59,539
♪ Ride like the wind ♪

88
00:04:01,274 --> 00:04:03,109
♪ Gonna ride like the wind ♪

89
00:04:04,010 --> 00:04:05,411
Whoo! [laughing]

90
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:09,048
[singing melody]

91
00:04:09,849 --> 00:04:11,584
- Whoo!
- [music stops abruptly]

92
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:14,487
[metal creaking, clanging]

93
00:04:16,322 --> 00:04:18,324
[wind whooshing]

94
00:04:21,127 --> 00:04:23,329
[motorcycle revving]

95
00:04:24,364 --> 00:04:27,866
[♪ "Ride Like the Wind"
continues playing faintly]

96
00:04:27,867 --> 00:04:29,502
[exhales sharply]
Andale.

97
00:04:32,572 --> 00:04:34,574
[metal clunking]

98
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:40,345
Fuck.

99
00:04:40,346 --> 00:04:43,082
- [metal clanging]
- Whoa! Fuck.

100
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:51,391
[metal scraping]

101
00:04:54,027 --> 00:04:56,229
[creaking]

102
00:04:58,531 --> 00:04:59,931
Whoa.

103
00:04:59,932 --> 00:05:02,267
♪ To get to the border
of Mexico ♪

104
00:05:02,268 --> 00:05:05,804
♪ So I'll ride like the wind ♪

105
00:05:05,805 --> 00:05:07,172
Fuck!

106
00:05:07,173 --> 00:05:09,375
- [music turning off]
- Okay.

107
00:05:10,643 --> 00:05:12,011
Shit.

108
00:05:14,614 --> 00:05:16,415
Go back.

109
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:18,950
[engine revving]

110
00:05:18,951 --> 00:05:20,219
Alright.

111
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:23,488
- [grunting]
- [engine revving]

112
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:25,257
[tires scraping]

113
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:26,326
Come on.

114
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,762
[engine revving]

115
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:37,503
- [banging]
- [muttering indistinctly]

116
00:05:39,205 --> 00:05:40,772
[turns off engine]

117
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:42,275
[Rue sighs]

118
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:53,719
Oh!

119
00:05:53,720 --> 00:05:55,288
[glass breaking]

120
00:05:56,689 --> 00:05:58,358
Ah. Fuck!

121
00:06:01,928 --> 00:06:03,829
[grunting]

122
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:06,065
Put all my weight...

123
00:06:09,235 --> 00:06:10,602
- [grunting]
- [horn honks]

124
00:06:10,603 --> 00:06:11,604
Ah!

125
00:06:17,677 --> 00:06:19,512
[softly] Oh, shit.

126
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:23,982
[metal creaking]

127
00:06:23,983 --> 00:06:26,185
- [wind whooshing]
- [Rue breathing heavily]

128
00:06:37,096 --> 00:06:39,865
[gasping, exclaiming]

129
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:42,068
Ah! Ah! Ah!

130
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:46,439
[♪ tense music playing]

131
00:06:53,012 --> 00:06:54,213
[exhales sharply]

132
00:06:56,949 --> 00:06:58,651
[metal creaking]

133
00:07:00,787 --> 00:07:02,655
Oh, shit. Ah, ah!

134
00:07:05,124 --> 00:07:08,161
Oh! Oh! Oh!

135
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,803
♪

136
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:23,376
There we go.

137
00:07:31,150 --> 00:07:33,119
Okay. Whew.

138
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,122
[wind whistling]

139
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:41,394
[♪ dramatic music playing]

140
00:07:43,663 --> 00:07:46,165
[hawk screeching]

141
00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:55,374
[whip cracks]

142
00:08:07,186 --> 00:08:14,193
[♪ dramatic music
continues playing]

143
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:36,615
[rooster crowing]

144
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:38,818
- [pig grunting]
- [cow mooing]

145
00:08:40,353 --> 00:08:42,288
[horse nickering]

146
00:08:55,234 --> 00:09:02,808
You want a cup of milk?

147
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:12,485
[yawning] Sure.

148
00:09:19,258 --> 00:09:21,527
Thank you.

149
00:09:29,168 --> 00:09:31,404
That's the best fucking milk
I've ever had.

150
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:33,573
It's Dahlia's.

151
00:09:37,109 --> 00:09:38,877
[Rue] Thank you, Dahlia.

152
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:40,713
[Dahlia mooing]

153
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,515
[Mr. Miller]
We wanna thank you,
Lord Jesus Christ,

154
00:09:43,516 --> 00:09:47,286
for giving us our daily bread
and forgiving us our trespasses.

155
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:51,189
And Lord, please guide
our new friend Ruby

156
00:09:51,190 --> 00:09:53,458
and her college newspaper
to help expose

157
00:09:53,459 --> 00:09:56,861
the-- the pure evil that's
pouring across our border

158
00:09:56,862 --> 00:10:00,732
and poisoning our great nation,
the United States of America.

159
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:01,968
Amen.

160
00:10:05,004 --> 00:10:06,137
Amen.

161
00:10:06,138 --> 00:10:07,607
- [all] Amen.
- [Mr. Miller] Let's eat.

162
00:10:08,474 --> 00:10:11,276
- Alright, pass the eggs.
- We're gonna help
with your plate, sweetie.

163
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:13,279
You know who
gets it first, Dad.

164
00:10:13,813 --> 00:10:15,513
[Mr. Miller]
This is our address.

165
00:10:15,514 --> 00:10:18,183
Will you be sure to send your
article when it's in the paper?

166
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:21,287
Yeah, as long as the commies
at college don't censor it.
[chuckles]

167
00:10:22,488 --> 00:10:24,890
- You're doing the Lord's work.
- Thank you.

168
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:27,158
- Hope to see you again soon.
- Thank you so much.

169
00:10:27,159 --> 00:10:28,994
- Good luck with everything.
- Yeah.

170
00:10:28,995 --> 00:10:32,297
- Bye, guys.
- [all] Bye.

171
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:34,500
- Wish you well.
- Thank you.

172
00:10:35,601 --> 00:10:36,968
- Aw.
- Safe travels.

173
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:38,269
- Thank you.
- God bless!

174
00:10:38,270 --> 00:10:39,371
Bye.

175
00:10:39,372 --> 00:10:41,574
[♪ whimsical vocalizing]

176
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:49,015
I just got my permit.

177
00:10:50,316 --> 00:10:52,518
[car starting]

178
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:04,363
[Mr. Miller]
God bless, Ruby.

179
00:11:05,598 --> 00:11:07,733
[Daisy] I've never been
on the internet.

180
00:11:09,335 --> 00:11:11,237
[Rue] You know, Daisy,
I think you got it made.

181
00:11:12,238 --> 00:11:14,639
[♪ "Love is Like Oxygen"
by Sweet playing on car radio]

182
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,609
But I can't help
but be curious.

183
00:11:18,577 --> 00:11:23,449
All the people out there
living big, exciting lives.

184
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,754
I'd trade spots with you
in a heartbeat.

185
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:32,091
Why?

186
00:11:35,995 --> 00:11:37,997
[radio volume increasing]

187
00:11:39,565 --> 00:11:44,369
♪ You get too much,
you get too high ♪

188
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:47,373
♪ Not enough,
and you're gonna die ♪

189
00:11:53,479 --> 00:11:54,680
[Rue] Thank you.

190
00:11:58,017 --> 00:11:59,584
You ought to come back out
in the spring

191
00:11:59,585 --> 00:12:01,120
and meet Dahlia's baby.

192
00:12:03,322 --> 00:12:04,657
I just might.

193
00:12:13,432 --> 00:12:19,037
- Oh, shit, qué pasó!
- [laughing] USA.

194
00:12:19,038 --> 00:12:21,339
- Hey, USA, USA.
- USA.

195
00:12:21,340 --> 00:12:27,480
[group]
USA! USA! USA! USA! USA!

196
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:33,786
[♪ hopeful music playing]

197
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:54,740
[♪ hopeful music
continues playing]

198
00:13:07,486 --> 00:13:13,726
[rattlesnake rattling]

199
00:13:24,737 --> 00:13:26,939
[metal fan rattling]

200
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:30,643
[wind whooshing]

201
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:51,663
[TV playing faintly]

202
00:13:51,664 --> 00:13:53,666
[bird chirping]

203
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:58,603
[bird calling]

204
00:13:58,604 --> 00:14:00,940
[bird babbling, whistling]

205
00:14:02,474 --> 00:14:04,510
[squawking, calling]

206
00:14:09,248 --> 00:14:11,182
[Laurie] Hello, Rue.

207
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,751
- [bird chirps]
- Hey, baby.

208
00:14:13,752 --> 00:14:16,721
- Where's my car?
- [Rue] I had to leave it behind.

209
00:14:16,722 --> 00:14:19,959
[Laurie]
Hm, I guess I'll just
add it to your tab then.

210
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:22,861
[Rue] A few years
after high school,

211
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:24,729
I was working
at a smoke shop.

212
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:26,764
[customer]
Could I just get
a raw cone, please?

213
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:28,033
[Rue] Yeah, for sure.

214
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:33,072
You can keep
the change actually, thanks.

215
00:14:34,340 --> 00:14:35,541
Okay.

216
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:47,051
[chuckles] Laurie, hey.

217
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,821
- How are you?
- You owe me money.

218
00:14:49,822 --> 00:14:52,257
No, I-- I know, yeah.
I was gonna pay you back.

219
00:14:52,258 --> 00:14:53,858
- You were?
- Yeah.

220
00:14:53,859 --> 00:14:56,161
Um, but then, you know,
you-- you moved.

221
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:59,797
[chuckles] I don't really have,
like, ten grand right now.

222
00:14:59,798 --> 00:15:02,233
Oh, you don't owe me
ten grand, silly.

223
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:03,868
- I don't?
- No.

224
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:08,006
Um, you did 46 months ago,
and, um, now,

225
00:15:08,007 --> 00:15:12,043
$10,000 at a 20%
monthly interest rate

226
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:16,882
over 46 months means that
you actually owe me, uh...

227
00:15:17,616 --> 00:15:21,720
$43,887,000.

228
00:15:23,322 --> 00:15:25,791
Uh, $43 million?

229
00:15:26,659 --> 00:15:29,160
[Laurie]
I'll settle for 100,000.

230
00:15:29,161 --> 00:15:32,064
But I bet you don't
have that either.

231
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:38,269
[Rue] And that is how
I became a drug mule.

232
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:40,038
[car horns honking]

233
00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:41,572
[dogs barking]

234
00:15:41,573 --> 00:15:44,777
[♪ dramatic Western music
playing]

235
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:54,653
[people chattering]

236
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:05,965
♪

237
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:21,347
[Uno] Swallow.

238
00:16:21,847 --> 00:16:25,616
Um, I don't-- I don't really
think that's possible.

239
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:27,285
[Uno chuckles]

240
00:16:27,286 --> 00:16:28,586
Claro que sí.

241
00:16:28,587 --> 00:16:30,289
Disfruta.

242
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:36,929
[cigarette sizzling]

243
00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,305
[Rue]
The most important thing...

244
00:16:47,106 --> 00:16:49,675
is to make sure each balloon
is properly sealed.

245
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:57,049
[grunting]

246
00:16:59,118 --> 00:17:00,818
[gulping]

247
00:17:00,819 --> 00:17:02,254
[gagging, coughing]

248
00:17:05,758 --> 00:17:06,959
[gagging]

249
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,160
[gagging]

250
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:13,298
After a few runs,
I decided to bring a friend.

251
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:19,604
[gulping, retching]

252
00:17:19,605 --> 00:17:20,739
[Rue] Fuck.

253
00:17:23,308 --> 00:17:24,376
[gagging]

254
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:32,885
[retching continues]

255
00:17:36,688 --> 00:17:38,923
[coughing] Ugh.

256
00:17:38,924 --> 00:17:40,558
The danger
of body packing is...

257
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,893
[sighs]

258
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:44,128
...if a balloon breaks,

259
00:17:44,129 --> 00:17:45,364
you die.

260
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:52,805
[speaking Spanish]

261
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:07,086
[indistinct chatter]

262
00:18:13,692 --> 00:18:15,726
[Rue] Faye, get your ass
in the car.

263
00:18:15,727 --> 00:18:17,628
Okay, we gotta cross by 3:00.

264
00:18:17,629 --> 00:18:20,833
[♪ dramatic music playing]

265
00:18:23,335 --> 00:18:26,038
[car horns honking]

266
00:18:32,444 --> 00:18:36,448
[police radio chatter]

267
00:18:42,754 --> 00:18:45,156
- [farting]
- Yo.

268
00:18:45,157 --> 00:18:46,324
Sorry.

269
00:18:46,325 --> 00:18:49,360
- Don't, man.
- I can only clench for so long.

270
00:18:49,361 --> 00:18:51,229
Yeah, I know,
but you gotta keep that shit

271
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,332
up there, alright?
Breathe through it.

272
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:56,234
- [farting]
- Damn!

273
00:18:56,235 --> 00:18:59,137
- Sorry.
- Faye, the fuck did you eat?

274
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:01,272
- [speaking Spanish]
- I'm good, thank you.

275
00:19:01,273 --> 00:19:02,773
No, gracias.

276
00:19:02,774 --> 00:19:04,576
[dog barking]

277
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,548
Turn the engine off, please.

278
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,518
- [engine stopping]
- Passports.

279
00:19:18,690 --> 00:19:20,391
What were you ladies
doing in Mexico?

280
00:19:20,392 --> 00:19:22,860
Uh... [chuckles]
I was just showing my girl

281
00:19:22,861 --> 00:19:24,963
how the mamacitas
do it down here. [chuckles]

282
00:19:29,735 --> 00:19:32,004
- Ruby Bennett?
- That's me.

283
00:19:33,238 --> 00:19:34,406
Faye Valentine?

284
00:19:36,308 --> 00:19:37,309
You have fun?

285
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:39,378
No.

286
00:19:41,346 --> 00:19:43,015
[Ruby chuckles]

287
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,923
[dog barking]

288
00:19:53,992 --> 00:19:55,993
[dog sniffing]

289
00:19:55,994 --> 00:19:59,198
[♪ tense music playing]

290
00:20:04,336 --> 00:20:06,271
[dog sniffing]

291
00:20:12,377 --> 00:20:14,379
♪

292
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:28,327
- Welcome to America.
- Thank you, sir.

293
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:31,363
[car starting]

294
00:20:36,368 --> 00:20:37,969
- [birds squawking]
- [loud farting]

295
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:40,037
Laurie! Harley!
She's about ready to blow.

296
00:20:40,038 --> 00:20:43,507
- [Rue] [straining] Oh yeah.
- Get the strainer.
It's in the dishwasher.

297
00:20:43,508 --> 00:20:45,076
- [Rue panting]
- My bad.

298
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,078
- Come on, bro.
- [farting continues]

299
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:49,180
- [Rue] Oh, shit.
- Hang in there.

300
00:20:49,181 --> 00:20:50,348
- Okay.
- Hang in there.

301
00:20:50,349 --> 00:20:52,149
- Okay. Okay.
- Okay, I got you.

302
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:53,284
- [Rue groaning]
- The fuck are you doing?

303
00:20:53,285 --> 00:20:55,454
- Just breathe.
- I had an accident.

304
00:20:56,388 --> 00:20:58,923
- You better get the bucket.
- [Rue] Okay.

305
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:00,492
[TV playing faintly]

306
00:21:01,393 --> 00:21:02,827
[bucket clanging]

307
00:21:02,828 --> 00:21:04,195
[Rue] And that,
ladies and gentlemen...

308
00:21:04,196 --> 00:21:06,163
- Damn!
- ...is how fentanyl

309
00:21:06,164 --> 00:21:08,267
is smuggled
into the United States.

310
00:21:12,437 --> 00:21:14,940
[indistinct chatter]

311
00:21:17,876 --> 00:21:20,244
After Fezco's house
got raided,

312
00:21:20,245 --> 00:21:22,179
Laurie left East Highland
and went into business

313
00:21:22,180 --> 00:21:24,749
with her cousin Harley
and his son Wayne.

314
00:21:24,750 --> 00:21:27,018
[indistinct chatter]

315
00:21:27,019 --> 00:21:28,719
I'm not saying
they're inbred...

316
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,221
[babbling]

317
00:21:30,222 --> 00:21:32,690
- ...but I have my suspicions.
- Appreciate it.

318
00:21:32,691 --> 00:21:34,258
Looks good, Faye.

319
00:21:34,259 --> 00:21:35,760
[Harley] Here's to Rue.

320
00:21:35,761 --> 00:21:38,029
You haven't been killed
or caught yet.

321
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,997
[chuckles]

322
00:21:39,998 --> 00:21:43,367
Praise the Lord.
[laughing]

323
00:21:43,368 --> 00:21:45,636
[Rue] I'd done a dozen runs
over the course of two years

324
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:49,007
and somehow ended up
their number-one mule.

325
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:52,244
[Wayne]
Guess you finally found
something you're good at.

326
00:21:53,779 --> 00:21:55,981
[rat squeaking]

327
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:01,386
You think Wayne
liked the spaghetti?

328
00:22:03,088 --> 00:22:06,490
[Rue]
Mm, I think Wayne likes you.

329
00:22:06,491 --> 00:22:07,826
[chuckles softly]

330
00:22:08,794 --> 00:22:12,930
You know, he's trying to get
out of the drug business.

331
00:22:12,931 --> 00:22:14,733
[Rue] Yeah,
I don't know about that.

332
00:22:17,703 --> 00:22:19,170
He's been saving up.

333
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:21,073
That's why he's got
a lot of money in his safe.

334
00:22:24,343 --> 00:22:25,744
What safe?

335
00:22:26,945 --> 00:22:28,346
[Faye]
The big one in his basement.

336
00:22:28,347 --> 00:22:30,114
He wants to get
into avocados,

337
00:22:30,115 --> 00:22:34,152
and you can make
a lot of money with avocados.

338
00:22:42,594 --> 00:22:44,528
What else does he have
in that safe?

339
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:48,166
Uh, I don't know.
Important stuff.

340
00:22:49,034 --> 00:22:51,570
- Where's the key?
- On his belt.

341
00:22:53,271 --> 00:22:56,574
What if there was a way to,
like, take off his belt?

342
00:22:56,575 --> 00:22:58,577
[both laughing]

343
00:23:00,946 --> 00:23:02,546
I think I can
figure that out.

344
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:03,748
[rooster crowing]

345
00:23:03,749 --> 00:23:06,283
[Rue] In between runs,
I'd pick up extra cash

346
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:07,652
driving for Uber.

347
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:10,287
[engine starting]

348
00:23:10,288 --> 00:23:14,158
[♪ "Sunset and Vine"
by Waylon Jennings playing]

349
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:18,229
♪ I left the old farm
down in Texas ♪

350
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:21,733
♪ And bummed
all around for a time ♪

351
00:23:22,434 --> 00:23:26,670
♪ Then one day
I found myself staring ♪

352
00:23:26,671 --> 00:23:30,775
♪ At a sign that read
Sunset and Vine ♪

353
00:23:30,776 --> 00:23:33,043
♪ The big cars
and the view... ♪

354
00:23:33,044 --> 00:23:34,612
[passenger]
This city is crumbling.

355
00:23:34,613 --> 00:23:38,482
Crime is out of control.
Somebody's got to do something.

356
00:23:38,483 --> 00:23:39,683
Yeah, totally.

357
00:23:39,684 --> 00:23:42,486
♪ I decided to be
a great actor ♪

358
00:23:42,487 --> 00:23:44,722
- Ooh, up here on the right.
- Oh, okay.

359
00:23:44,723 --> 00:23:47,124
♪ On the corner
of Sunset and Vine ♪

360
00:23:47,125 --> 00:23:49,193
Alright. Here you go.

361
00:23:49,194 --> 00:23:51,529
- Stay out of trouble.
- Yeah, will do, Batman.

362
00:23:51,530 --> 00:23:52,763
- [horns honking]
- [Batman sighs]

363
00:23:52,764 --> 00:23:54,432
I don't know,
why are we still auditioning?

364
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:57,335
Boy Wonder.
Hey, babe, how are you?

365
00:24:03,208 --> 00:24:04,542
[knocking]

366
00:24:04,543 --> 00:24:06,711
[in low voice]
Yo, Howard!
It's Bennett, open up!

367
00:24:12,317 --> 00:24:13,785
- Hey!
- [chuckles] Hey.

368
00:24:14,486 --> 00:24:17,254
- How was Arizona?
- Um, yeah, no, it was great.

369
00:24:17,255 --> 00:24:18,856
Uh, just got
to hang out with Gia,

370
00:24:18,857 --> 00:24:20,157
and she's-- she's doing good.

371
00:24:20,158 --> 00:24:21,759
She's, like, top of her class.

372
00:24:21,760 --> 00:24:22,828
So was I.

373
00:24:23,829 --> 00:24:25,095
I know.

374
00:24:25,096 --> 00:24:27,064
[Rue]
Sometimes Lexi would
let me crash on her couch.

375
00:24:27,065 --> 00:24:29,500
[teapot whistling]

376
00:24:29,501 --> 00:24:31,535
But it always came
with a lecture.

377
00:24:31,536 --> 00:24:33,270
[Lexi] What are your
long-term goals?

378
00:24:33,271 --> 00:24:35,806
[Rue] And since
I couldn't be honest
about what I'd been up to...

379
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:36,941
Uh...

380
00:24:36,942 --> 00:24:38,175
...I'd be vague.

381
00:24:38,176 --> 00:24:40,878
Right now, it's kinda
just a day at a time.

382
00:24:40,879 --> 00:24:43,280
You have to plan for the future,
because pretty soon

383
00:24:43,281 --> 00:24:45,649
Uber drivers
are gonna be extinct.

384
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,685
It's all gonna be
automated, like AI.

385
00:24:47,686 --> 00:24:49,654
They're not gonna need
people like you.

386
00:24:51,189 --> 00:24:52,390
Right.

387
00:24:56,528 --> 00:24:59,363
You know, I met these,
uh, these Christians

388
00:24:59,364 --> 00:25:01,365
on a homestead in Texas.

389
00:25:01,366 --> 00:25:03,300
Christians in Texas?

390
00:25:03,301 --> 00:25:07,004
It was a drop-off.
But, yeah, the Miller family.

391
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:08,573
I can't stop thinking
about them.

392
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:13,344
There's like six kids,
and they lived on a farm

393
00:25:13,345 --> 00:25:15,145
with like a bunch of animals.

394
00:25:15,146 --> 00:25:17,848
And no technology.
No nothin'.

395
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:21,252
And I genuinely think that
they were the happiest people

396
00:25:21,253 --> 00:25:22,520
I've ever met in my life.

397
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:24,488
'Cause they're in a cult.

398
00:25:24,489 --> 00:25:26,391
Oh, well,
maybe that's the answer.

399
00:25:27,692 --> 00:25:28,792
Christianity?

400
00:25:28,793 --> 00:25:31,962
I just feel like
if I grew up religious,

401
00:25:31,963 --> 00:25:33,497
maybe my life
would be better.

402
00:25:33,498 --> 00:25:36,100
Well, I'm not gonna be
friends with a Christian.

403
00:25:36,101 --> 00:25:37,302
[scoffs] Why?

404
00:25:38,303 --> 00:25:40,405
'Cause they're judgmental.

405
00:25:47,078 --> 00:25:48,780
You know,
you really should call Fez.

406
00:25:50,882 --> 00:25:52,317
Yeah, I know.

407
00:25:53,385 --> 00:25:55,619
I feel guilty,
but I just-- I haven't--

408
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:57,588
I haven't had any time,
I've been really busy.

409
00:25:57,589 --> 00:25:59,823
Yeah, well,
you're free today.

410
00:25:59,824 --> 00:26:03,461
This is rare. Like, I-- I work,
like, seven days a week.

411
00:26:04,429 --> 00:26:06,196
Yeah, well, he misses you.

412
00:26:06,197 --> 00:26:07,865
Did he say that?

413
00:26:07,866 --> 00:26:10,435
- Multiple times.
- Mm.

414
00:26:11,202 --> 00:26:14,438
I don't know,
my hours and his hours

415
00:26:14,439 --> 00:26:16,740
don't really line up,
so it's hard.

416
00:26:16,741 --> 00:26:19,276
No, just like, pick up
the phone and call him.

417
00:26:19,277 --> 00:26:20,979
It's not like
he's going anywhere.

418
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:23,582
He's in prison for 30 years.

419
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:27,985
[Rue] Lexi was
working in Hollywood

420
00:26:27,986 --> 00:26:29,521
on a nighttime soap.

421
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:35,994
Her boss, Patty Lance,
was an industry legend.

422
00:26:36,828 --> 00:26:39,965
[Patty]
Writers are the engineers
of the human soul.

423
00:26:40,899 --> 00:26:45,235
People underestimate
the power of entertainment.

424
00:26:45,236 --> 00:26:47,504
What you see on television

425
00:26:47,505 --> 00:26:50,875
directly impacts the way
we see one another.

426
00:26:52,310 --> 00:26:55,913
The decisions we make
at home, in schools,

427
00:26:55,914 --> 00:27:00,417
and more importantly,
what we do at the ballot box.

428
00:27:00,418 --> 00:27:02,119
- [people snapping]
- Okay?

429
00:27:02,120 --> 00:27:06,790
That means it's really important
that we get 712 together.

430
00:27:06,791 --> 00:27:09,494
- [people snapping]
- [Rue] Lexi felt right at home.

431
00:27:10,095 --> 00:27:13,464
She was surrounded
by smart, creative people
who cared about the world.

432
00:27:13,465 --> 00:27:15,399
This election.

433
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:18,335
It's giving me
so much anxiety.

434
00:27:18,336 --> 00:27:20,304
[Rue]
Unlike her sister,
who was living

435
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:22,806
in some right-wing
suburban bubble.

436
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:26,011
[♪ "(How Much is That)
Doggie in the Window"
by Patti Page playing]

437
00:27:27,779 --> 00:27:32,082
♪ How much is that doggie
in the window ♪

438
00:27:32,083 --> 00:27:33,717
[dog barking]

439
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:39,323
♪ The one with
the waggly tail ♪

440
00:27:39,324 --> 00:27:40,658
[Rue]
She spent her free time

441
00:27:40,659 --> 00:27:42,292
trying to become
TikTok famous.

442
00:27:42,293 --> 00:27:43,961
- ♪ In the window ♪
- [panting]

443
00:27:43,962 --> 00:27:47,965
- [dog barking]
- ♪ I do hope that doggie ♪

444
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:50,101
♪ Is for sale ♪

445
00:27:55,573 --> 00:27:58,676
♪ How much is that doggie ♪

446
00:27:58,677 --> 00:28:00,544
♪ In the window ♪

447
00:28:00,545 --> 00:28:03,081
[housekeeper] Very nice,
Miss Cassie, very nice.

448
00:28:04,382 --> 00:28:06,884
And wiggle, wiggle, wiggle.

449
00:28:06,885 --> 00:28:09,987
♪ How much is that doggie ♪

450
00:28:09,988 --> 00:28:12,289
- ♪ In the window ♪
- [dog barking]

451
